# Form Filling

The PDFViewer enables users to fill interactive forms directly in PDF documents. You can display and edit form fields such as text boxes, checkboxes, radio buttons, and dropdowns.

## Supported Form Fields

The PDFViewer supports the following form field types:

* `TextBox`
* `CheckBox`
* `RadioButton`
* `DropdownList`
* `ListBox`
* `Button`

>caption Edit Form Fields and Download the Updated PDF File

`````Razor
<TelerikPdfViewer Width="100%"
                  AnnotationMode="@AnnotationMode"
                  Height="700px"
                  Data="@FileData">
</TelerikPdfViewer>

@code {
    private byte[] FileData { get; set; }
    private PdfViewerAnnotationMode AnnotationMode { get; set; } = PdfViewerAnnotationMode.EnableForms;

    private static string DummyPdfBase64 => @"";

    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        FileData = Convert.FromBase64String(DummyPdfBase64);
    }
}
`````
